-- Banco Espirito, Credit Agricole: European Equity Preview
-- B y   J o s e p h   C i o l l i
-- 2012-03-30T04:00:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-29/banco-espirito-credit-agricole-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index (SXXP)  fell 1.3 percent to 260.74. The
 Stoxx 50 Index (SX5P)  decreased 1.2 percent to 2,439.73. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro,
dropped 1.8 percent to 2,452.74.  Allianz SE (ALV)  (ALV GY):  Europe ’s biggest insurer offered less
than 200 million euros ($266 million) for Groupama SA’s GAN
Eurocourtage unit, Financial Times Deutschland reported, citing
unidentified people close to the  insurance industry . Groupama
had wanted to raise 700 million euros from the sale, the
newspaper reported. The shares declined 2.3 percent to 89.30
euros.  Banco Espirito Santo SA (BES)  :  Portugal ’s biggest
publicly traded bank in market value had its debt rating lowered
one level to Ba3 by Moody’s Investors Service. It took the same
action for  Banco BPI SA (BPI)  . Espirito Santo dropped 3.2
percent to 1.41 euros. BPI fell 2.3 percent to 50 euro cents.  Brisa-Auto Estradas de Portgual SA  (BRI PL): Shareholders
with a combined 50 stake of Portugal’s biggest toll-road
operator offered to buy the rest of the company in a deal
valuing it at 1.6 billion euros. The shares decreased 0.6
percent to 2.35 euros.  Credit Agricole SA (ACA)  : The French bank’s corporate
and investment bank entered exclusive talks with Citic
Securities Co.,  China ’s largest broker by market value, to sell
the remaining 80.1 percent stake in its CLSA brokerage unit. The
shares fell 2.8 percent to 4.62 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joseph Ciolli in New York at 
